id: pm-pxx0
title: Implement local telemetry queue retention_days TTL cleanup
description: retention_days exists in telemetry settings but no cleanup logic prunes old queue entries or events from disk.
type: Issue
status: open
priority: 3
tags[3]: "audit:2026-04-26",pm-cli,telemetry
created_at: "2026-04-26T14:52:27.856Z"
updated_at: "2026-04-26T14:52:27.856Z"
deadline: "2026-05-10T14:52:27.856Z"
author: audit-agent
estimated_minutes: 30
acceptance_criteria: Stale queue entries older than retention_days are pruned during flush cycles.
parent: pm-lnq3
body: The events.jsonl queue file grows unbounded if the remote endpoint is unreachable. retention_days should be used to prune stale entries and cap disk usage.
